1028
01:51:13,453 --> 01:51:14,565
The Whites?

1029
01:51:16,685 --> 01:51:18,506
No, Strelnikov.

1030
01:51:20,204 --> 01:51:22,625
Well, then, you must have done something.

1031
01:51:23,244 --> 01:51:24,967
It wasn't us, Comrade.

1032
01:51:25,228 --> 01:51:27,595
The commander said
we'd sold horses to the Whites.

1033
01:51:27,660 --> 01:51:29,864
It wasn't us, it was those pigs in Kuniko.

1034
01:51:29,996 --> 01:51:31,883
We told him, but he didn't believe us.

1035
01:51:31,947 --> 01:51:33,573
I expect you were lying.

1036
01:51:33,642 --> 01:51:35,715
- As God's my witness.
- But he isn't.

1037
01:51:37,675 --> 01:51:39,748
Commander Strelnikov is a great man.

1038
01:51:41,354 --> 01:51:44,737
A commander, Sasha,
and he lives on bread and water.

1039
01:51:45,322 --> 01:51:46,336
Does he?

1040
01:51:47,211 --> 01:51:48,617
I don't know. They say so.

1041
01:51:48,682 --> 01:51:49,630
It's true.

1042
01:51:49,707 --> 01:51:51,681
No one knows where he comes from.

1043
01:51:52,169 --> 01:51:54,079
And they never know where he is.

1044
01:51:54,217 --> 01:51:56,356
- He's back up the line.
- Yes?

1045
01:51:59,273 --> 01:52:00,647
Someone's for it.

1046
01:52:03,113 --> 01:52:04,738
Oh, really, not again!

1047
01:52:06,279 --> 01:52:07,556
What this time?

1048
01:52:17,384 --> 01:52:19,937
Never mind, Father.
Get a good night's sleep.

1049
01:52:24,935 --> 01:52:26,658
I know what I'm going to do.

1050
01:52:48,485 --> 01:52:49,467
Look!

1051
01:52:50,597 --> 01:52:51,774
The Urals.

1052
01:52:53,573 --> 01:52:56,441
Look, Sasha, look.
That's where we're going, darling.

1053
01:52:56,772 --> 01:52:59,161
Through the mountains and into the forest.

1054
01:52:59,396 --> 01:53:01,305
Then it'll be much warmer still.

1055
01:53:02,500 --> 01:53:04,889
Will there be wolves in the forest?

1056
01:53:28,674 --> 01:53:30,201
Strelnikov!

1057
01:53:37,953 --> 01:53:39,382
That's Strelnikov.

1058
01:58:19,427 --> 01:58:20,425
Daddy!

1059
01:58:23,427 --> 01:58:24,903
What's that noise?

1060
01:58:26,113 --> 01:58:27,704
It's only a waterfall.

1061
01:58:27,906 --> 01:58:29,343
No, the other noise.

1062
01:58:33,507 --> 01:58:34,745
Guns, Sasha.

1063
01:58:35,588 --> 01:58:36,990
Are they fighting?

1064
01:58:37,190 --> 01:58:39,665
They must be. It's a long way away.

1065
01:58:40,345 --> 01:58:41,630
Let's go to sleep.

1066
01:59:29,984 --> 01:59:31,029
Get him!

1067
01:59:37,187 --> 01:59:38,271
Look!

1068
01:59:46,345 --> 01:59:47,430
Is that all?

1069
01:59:47,507 --> 01:59:48,790
That's all.

1070
01:59:56,588 --> 01:59:57,863
Bring him.

1071
02:00:09,984 --> 02:00:11,711
Who sent you here, Zhivago?

1072
02:00:12,142 --> 02:00:14,185
No one sent me here, Commander.

1073
02:00:14,310 --> 02:00:16,467
I'm going to Yuriatin
with my wife and child.

1074
02:00:16,544 --> 02:00:18,225
They're on the train from Moscow.

1075
02:00:18,312 --> 02:00:19,864
Yes, we've checked that.

1076
02:00:20,391 --> 02:00:20,987
Then?

1077
02:00:21,072 --> 02:00:24,745
You put your knife with a fork and a spoon
and it looks quite innocuous.

1078
02:00:24,831 --> 02:00:28,150
Perhaps you travel with a wife and child
for the same reason?

1079
02:00:30,192 --> 02:00:31,151
No.

1080
02:00:31,429 --> 02:00:35,264
Yuriatin is occupied by White Guards.
Is that why you're going there?

1081
02:00:35,744 --> 02:00:38,189
No. We're going on to Varykino.

1082
02:00:38,543 --> 02:00:41,069
Not through Yuriatin. It's under shellfire.

1083
02:00:41,585 --> 02:00:43,667
Commander, I'm not a White agent.

1084
02:00:45,104 --> 02:00:46,830
No, I don't think you are.

1085
02:00:47,071 --> 02:00:49,910
All right, Kolya. Thank you, Comrades.
Sit down, Doctor.

1086
02:00:49,986 --> 02:00:50,906
Take it.

1087
02:00:52,469 --> 02:00:55,990
It's not as silly as it seems.
There have been one or two attempts.

1088
02:01:01,591 --> 02:01:02,868
Are you the poet?

1089
02:01:03,623 --> 02:01:04,583
Yes.

1090
02:01:04,948 --> 02:01:06,788
I used to admire your poetry.

1091
02:01:06,865 --> 02:01:07,863
Thank you.

1092
02:01:08,428 --> 02:01:10,107
I shouldn't admire it now.

1093
02:01:10,145 --> 02:01:13,022
I should find it absurdly personal.
Don't you agree?

1094
02:01:13,991 --> 02:01:17,346
Feelings, insights, affections.
It's suddenly trivial, now.

1095
02:01:18,910 --> 02:01:20,789
You don't agree. You're wrong.

1096
02:01:21,029 --> 02:01:23,149
The personal life is dead in Russia.

1097
02:01:24,186 --> 02:01:25,710
History has killed it.

1098
02:01:26,986 --> 02:01:28,905
I can see how you might hate me.

1099
02:01:30,583 --> 02:01:33,909
I hate everything you say,
but not enough to kill you for it.

1100
02:01:36,423 --> 02:01:37,784
You have a brother?

1101
02:01:37,871 --> 02:01:38,704
Yevgraf?.

1102
02:01:38,782 --> 02:01:40,709
Yevgraf. Yes. The policeman.

1103
02:01:40,987 --> 02:01:42,385
I didn't know that.

1104
02:01:42,502 --> 02:01:45,630
Perhaps not. A "secret" policeman.
Did he send you here?

1105
02:01:45,669 --> 02:01:46,742
Yevgraf?.

1106
02:01:46,943 --> 02:01:48,582
No, Yevgraf's a Bolshevik.

1107
02:01:52,908 --> 02:01:55,669
I don't know anything about these things.

1108
02:01:55,745 --> 02:01:57,463
Oh, you know a great deal.

1109
02:01:58,625 --> 02:02:00,666
When you came in you recognized me.

1110
02:02:01,144 --> 02:02:02,179
How?

1111
02:02:02,507 --> 02:02:04,347
Has someone shown you photographs?

1112
02:02:04,424 --> 02:02:05,424
No.

1113
02:02:05,702 --> 02:02:07,869
I am certain that you recognized me.

1114
02:02:10,305 --> 02:02:12,386
I've seen you before, Commander.

1115
02:02:13,182 --> 02:02:14,151
When?

1116
02:02:14,506 --> 02:02:15,790
Six years ago.

1117
02:02:16,423 --> 02:02:17,546
Go on.

1118
02:02:17,986 --> 02:02:19,385
Christmas Eve. You--

1119
02:02:20,585 --> 02:02:21,784
You were there?

1120
02:02:22,426 --> 02:02:24,268
Or, has someone told you this?

1121
02:02:24,900 --> 02:02:27,789
I attended to the man
who was injured by your wife.

1122
02:02:28,625 --> 02:02:30,464
Why do you call her my wife?

1123
02:02:31,749 --> 02:02:33,064
I met her again.

1124
02:02:33,428 --> 02:02:35,949
We served together on the Ukranian Front.

1125
02:02:36,140 --> 02:02:38,749
If she's with you,
I'm sure she'd vouch for me.

1126
02:02:39,104 --> 02:02:41,147
I haven't seen her since the war.

1127
02:02:42,144 --> 02:02:43,466
She's in Yuriatin.

1128
02:02:46,708 --> 02:02:47,909
Yuriatin!

1129
02:02:49,384 --> 02:02:54,029
The private life is dead,
for a man with any manhood.

1130
02:02:55,186 --> 02:02:58,141
We saw a sample of your manhood
on the way, a place called Mink.

1131
02:02:58,228 --> 02:03:00,020
They were selling horses to the Whites.

1132
02:03:00,068 --> 02:03:00,940
No.

1133
02:03:01,267 --> 02:03:03,059
It seems you burned the wrong village.

1134
02:03:03,107 --> 02:03:05,066
They always say that.
And what does it matter?

1135
02:03:05,143 --> 02:03:07,865
A village betrays us, a village is burnt.
The point's made.

1136
02:03:08,181 --> 02:03:10,063
Your point, their village.

1137
02:03:10,503 --> 02:03:11,663
Kolya!

1138
02:03:17,984 --> 02:03:21,225
And what will you do
with your wife and child in Varykino?

1139
02:03:21,302 --> 02:03:22,425
Just live.

1140
02:03:24,065 --> 02:03:25,942
Take him away. He's innocent.

1141
02:03:36,828 --> 02:03:38,027
You're lucky.

1142
02:04:11,104 --> 02:04:13,625
We've been diverted.
Do you know where we're going?

1143
02:04:13,702 --> 02:04:14,941
Varykino Halt.

1144
02:04:28,903 --> 02:04:29,900
Hello?

1145
02:04:33,745 --> 02:04:34,745
Hello?

1146
02:04:38,821 --> 02:04:40,105
How lovely!

1147
02:04:44,784 --> 02:04:46,222
Oh, how lovely!

1148
02:04:48,583 --> 02:04:49,627
Hello?

1149
02:04:50,624 --> 02:04:51,621
Hello?

1150
02:04:57,588 --> 02:04:59,306
Alexander Maximiovich?

1151
02:04:59,468 --> 02:05:00,427
Yes.

1152
02:05:01,299 --> 02:05:02,663
It's me, Petya.

1153
02:05:04,387 --> 02:05:05,185
Your Honor!

1154
02:05:05,261 --> 02:05:07,821
Now, now, now,
that's all done with, you know.

1155
02:05:10,141 --> 02:05:12,184
How do we get to the house, Petya?

1156
02:05:12,625 --> 02:05:14,140
As you always did, Your Honor.

1157
02:05:35,507 --> 02:05:36,783
Look, Sasha!

1158
02:05:41,389 --> 02:05:43,948
What is it, Petya? Forest fire?

1159
02:05:44,465 --> 02:05:46,499
Forest fire, Your Honor?

1160
02:05:46,584 --> 02:05:47,984
That's Yuriatin.

1161
02:05:48,742 --> 02:05:51,619
Poor souls.
First the Reds, then the Whites.

1162
02:05:52,023 --> 02:05:53,422
Now, the Reds again.

1163
02:05:54,065 --> 02:05:56,778
That's Strelnikov. His heart must be dead.

1164
02:06:00,740 --> 02:06:02,417
We'll soon be there, now, Sasha.

1165
02:06:02,466 --> 02:06:03,906
Another five miles.

1166
02:06:04,057 --> 02:06:07,703
Is it that far? One forgets.
How is the place?

1167
02:06:08,182 --> 02:06:11,981
Oh, well enough, Your Honor.
It's all locked up, you know.

1168
02:06:29,062 --> 02:06:30,182
Varykino!

1169
02:07:19,783 --> 02:07:21,624
All locked up, you see.

1170
02:07:27,979 --> 02:07:29,545
A body, styling itself.

1171
02:07:30,457 --> 02:07:33,304
The Yuriatin Committee
of Revolutionary Justice...

1172
02:07:33,985 --> 02:07:37,343
...has expropriated my house
in the name of the people.

1173
02:07:38,340 --> 02:07:39,625
Very well.

1174
02:07:39,739 --> 02:07:42,137
I'm one of the people, too!

1175
02:07:44,306 --> 02:07:46,865
Don't, Your Honor!
They'd call it counterrevolution.

1176
02:07:46,942 --> 02:07:48,860
- Get out of my way!
- Father, don't!

1177
02:07:48,937 --> 02:07:50,262
Petya brought us here.

1178
02:07:50,338 --> 02:07:52,744
That makes him
a counterrevolutionary, too.

1179
02:07:53,022 --> 02:07:55,066
They shoot counterrevolutionaries.

1180
02:08:07,618 --> 02:08:10,696
It's not the Reds in the town,
it's the Reds in the forest.

1181
02:08:10,936 --> 02:08:12,663
- Partisans.
- Here?

1182
02:08:12,778 --> 02:08:15,858
Who knows? They go where they want,
and they do what they want.

1183
02:08:15,943 --> 02:08:17,738
All we need is a roof, Petya.

1184
02:08:17,900 --> 02:08:20,585
And a bit of garden. Is there nowhere?

1185
02:08:25,379 --> 02:08:27,182
They didn't lock the cottage.

1186
02:08:37,302 --> 02:08:39,056
Oh, yes, we can manage here.

1187
02:08:43,140 --> 02:08:44,580
Oh, the stove works.

1188
02:08:45,904 --> 02:08:47,860
I'll find you a few sticks of furniture.

1189
02:08:47,936 --> 02:08:49,459
And some seed potatoes?

1190
02:08:50,420 --> 02:08:53,143
I'm afraid the garden is dreadfully run back.

1191
02:09:03,540 --> 02:09:04,817
Yes. Thank you.

1192
02:09:33,297 --> 02:09:34,582
Well done, my boy.

1193
02:09:34,901 --> 02:09:37,739
I must say, scratch a Russian
and you'll find a peasant.

1194
02:09:37,817 --> 02:09:39,265
I've always said so.

1195
02:09:39,418 --> 02:09:40,779
Well, you're wrong.

1196
02:09:40,818 --> 02:09:43,541
He works like a peasant,
but he isn't a peasant.

1197
02:09:43,618 --> 02:09:45,700
I don't mind, Tonya. Really.

1198
02:09:46,016 --> 02:09:48,096
- It's a good life.
- It certainly is.

1199
02:09:48,183 --> 02:09:52,460
I wouldn't be surprised if you two didn't
look back on this time as one of your best.

1200
02:09:53,697 --> 02:09:56,419
Awfully glad about the expected
new arrival, Yuri.

1201
02:09:57,139 --> 02:09:58,983
Anna was born here, you know.

1202
02:09:59,539 --> 02:10:01,217
Oh, no, I didn't know that.

1203
02:10:01,380 --> 02:10:02,981
Well, I'm terribly glad.

1204
02:10:03,776 --> 02:10:05,379
Here's winged Mercury.

1205
02:10:07,777 --> 02:10:09,741
Looks a bit down in the mouth.

1206
02:10:11,737 --> 02:10:12,896
Enter.

1207
02:10:13,337 --> 02:10:15,014
What news from Yuriatin?

1208
02:10:15,138 --> 02:10:18,735
There's no lard, no sugar.
Oil, next week, perhaps.

1209
02:10:18,975 --> 02:10:22,459
There's flour, salt, coffee and nails.

1210
02:10:27,417 --> 02:10:28,463
Bad news?

1211
02:10:29,383 --> 02:10:31,981
Oh, Lord, not another purge!

1212
02:10:32,096 --> 02:10:33,180
No.

1213
02:10:33,256 --> 02:10:34,579
Strelnikov's gone.

1214
02:10:35,337 --> 02:10:36,497
That's not bad news.

1215
02:10:36,536 --> 02:10:39,662
No. He's in Manchuria, they say.

1216
02:10:44,297 --> 02:10:45,744
That's the news.

1217
02:11:05,940 --> 02:11:07,495
They've shot the tsar.

1218
02:11:10,016 --> 02:11:11,455
And all his family.

1219
02:11:14,859 --> 02:11:17,092
Oh, that's a savage deed.

1220
02:11:20,334 --> 02:11:21,695
What's it for?

1221
02:11:24,573 --> 02:11:26,743
It's to show there's no going back.

1222
02:12:36,502 --> 02:12:38,573
Yuri, why don't you go to Yuriatin?

1223
02:12:39,496 --> 02:12:42,534
Yes, why don't you, my boy?
It'd do you good.

1224
02:12:44,020 --> 02:12:45,938
Why? What's in Yuriatin?

1225
02:12:46,494 --> 02:12:48,173
It isn't Petersburg.

1226
02:12:48,258 --> 02:12:50,253
A very decent little library...

1227
02:12:50,378 --> 02:12:51,895
...if it's still there.

1228
02:12:52,375 --> 02:12:53,622
I wish you would.

1229
02:12:55,538 --> 02:12:57,015
No, I don't think so.

1230
02:12:57,859 --> 02:12:59,700
Anyway, the roads are blocked.

1231
02:14:59,250 --> 02:15:00,211
Zhivago?

1232
02:15:04,258 --> 02:15:05,217
Yes.

1233
02:15:10,770 --> 02:15:11,893
How are you?

1234
02:15:13,532 --> 02:15:15,133
What are you doing here?

1235
02:15:15,576 --> 02:15:16,850
We're at Varykino.

1236
02:15:18,978 --> 02:15:19,975
Varykino?

1237
02:15:26,616 --> 02:15:27,775
Why Varykino?

1238
02:15:28,533 --> 02:15:30,614
Why not? We had to go somewhere.

1239
02:15:30,815 --> 02:15:32,253
But, here!

1240
02:15:33,298 --> 02:15:36,576
I came here to find my husband.
The one who was reported killed.

1241
02:15:36,652 --> 02:15:38,811
Strelnikov. I met him.

1242
02:15:40,413 --> 02:15:41,497
Met him?

1243
02:15:41,651 --> 02:15:42,656
Yes.

1244
02:17:11,857 --> 02:17:13,929
How long have you been living here?

1245
02:17:15,175 --> 02:17:16,374
About a year.

1246
02:17:21,056 --> 02:17:22,014
Alone?

1247
02:17:22,138 --> 02:17:23,174
With Katya.

1248
02:17:24,257 --> 02:17:25,572
Where's Katya now?

1249
02:17:26,330 --> 02:17:27,336
At school.

1250
02:18:15,779 --> 02:18:17,128
Is Tonya with you?

1251
02:18:18,454 --> 02:18:19,499
All of us.

1252
02:18:20,294 --> 02:18:21,253
Sasha?

1253
02:18:21,454 --> 02:18:22,576
Of course.

1254
02:18:27,448 --> 02:18:29,049
What are we going to do?

1255
02:18:29,690 --> 02:18:30,850
I don't know.

1256
02:19:42,770 --> 02:19:43,768
Yuri?

1257
02:19:45,649 --> 02:19:47,449
It's awfully early, isn't it?

1258
02:19:48,094 --> 02:19:49,291
Half past six.

1259
02:19:50,049 --> 02:19:51,448
What are you doing?

1260
02:19:52,129 --> 02:19:53,770
Nothing. Couldn't sleep.

1261
02:19:54,575 --> 02:19:56,089
Is anything the matter?

1262
02:19:56,493 --> 02:19:57,413
No.

1263
02:20:02,335 --> 02:20:03,774
Shall I get some tea?

1264
02:20:06,094 --> 02:20:07,131
Yes, do.

1265
02:21:25,087 --> 02:21:27,927
Hello. You are silly. We called and called.

1266
02:21:28,014 --> 02:21:30,371
- Did you? I didn't hear.
- Well, we did.

1267
02:21:32,885 --> 02:21:34,573
- Hello, Lara.
- Hello.

1268
02:21:37,134 --> 02:21:39,052
How's Olya Petrovna?

1269
02:21:39,130 --> 02:21:40,892
She gets worse and worse.

1270
02:21:41,047 --> 02:21:43,644
She gave us C.I. and arithmetic
all morning.

1271
02:21:43,846 --> 02:21:44,891
C.I.?

1272
02:21:45,286 --> 02:21:46,810
Civic Instruction.

1273
02:21:47,126 --> 02:21:48,133
Look.

1274
02:21:50,811 --> 02:21:52,968
- That's very good, Katya.
- Thank you.

1275
02:21:53,370 --> 02:21:54,771
It's the tsar.

1276
02:21:56,815 --> 02:21:58,935
The tsar was an enemy of the people.

1277
02:22:00,332 --> 02:22:03,373
Well, he didn't know he was an enemy
of the people, you know.

1278
02:22:03,449 --> 02:22:05,693
Well, he should have known, shouldn't he?

1279
02:22:05,769 --> 02:22:07,170
Yes, he should.

1280
02:22:07,727 --> 02:22:11,296
Fancy not knowing C.I.
Doesn't your little boy go to school?

1281
02:22:11,650 --> 02:22:12,608
Lunch.

1282
02:22:13,327 --> 02:22:14,372
Good.

1283
02:22:14,928 --> 02:22:16,330
Come on, you.

1284
02:22:46,605 --> 02:22:47,611
Smell.

1285
02:22:52,447 --> 02:22:54,414
This one's a prize-fighter.

1286
02:22:55,008 --> 02:22:55,965
Yuri!

1287
02:22:58,249 --> 02:22:59,448
Wait a minute.

1288
02:23:00,329 --> 02:23:01,289
There.

1289
02:23:19,605 --> 02:23:21,570
I'm going in to Yuriatin, darling--

1290
02:23:21,647 --> 02:23:22,732
What? Now?

1291
02:23:22,809 --> 02:23:26,012
Yes, I want to get some morphine,
disinfectant...

1292
02:23:26,164 --> 02:23:27,728
I shan't need morphine.

1293
02:23:27,843 --> 02:23:29,003
You never know.

1294
02:23:29,091 --> 02:23:30,568
Well, I shan't need it today.

1295
02:23:30,645 --> 02:23:33,367
No. But, it's pretty close.
I hadn't realized it.

1296
02:23:35,525 --> 02:23:37,972
- You'll be back before it's dark?
- Long before.

1297
02:23:50,813 --> 02:23:53,449
Yes, yes, my darling. Do what's best.

1298
02:23:54,090 --> 02:23:55,684
I'm not coming back.

1299
02:23:55,847 --> 02:23:57,131
I understand.

1300
02:23:57,610 --> 02:23:59,013
But, never, Lara.

1301
02:24:00,364 --> 02:24:01,728
Do you understand?

1302
02:24:03,165 --> 02:24:04,487
Do you believe me?

1303
02:25:04,370 --> 02:25:06,728
Comrade Doctor, I need a medical officer.

1304
02:25:06,766 --> 02:25:09,328
Sorry. I have a wife and child in Varykino.

1305
02:25:09,605 --> 02:25:11,371
And a mistress in Yuriatin.

1306
02:25:13,883 --> 02:25:16,481
Comrade Medical Officer,
we are Red Partisans...

1307
02:25:16,644 --> 02:25:18,563
...and we shoot deserters. Up!

1308
02:25:31,251 --> 02:25:32,209
Up!

1309
02:26:06,043 --> 02:26:08,288
- Where are you taking me?
- To the Front.

1310
02:26:09,286 --> 02:26:11,809
- And where is the Front?
- Good question.

1311
02:26:11,848 --> 02:26:14,571
The Front is wherever there are
enemies of the Revolution.

1312
02:26:14,647 --> 02:26:16,564
Wherever there is one gang
of White Guards...

1313
02:26:16,642 --> 02:26:19,528
...one battalion of foreign interventionists,
that is the Front.

1314
02:26:19,606 --> 02:26:23,009
Wherever there is one resentful
bourgeois, one unreliable schoolmaster...

1315
02:26:23,047 --> 02:26:25,446
...one dubious poet hugging his private life.

1316
02:26:25,962 --> 02:26:27,564
That, too, is the Front.

1317
02:26:29,283 --> 02:26:31,010
How long are you going to keep me?

1318
02:26:31,047 --> 02:26:32,486
For as long as we need you.

1319
02:27:20,686 --> 02:27:21,645
Now!

1320
02:27:30,564 --> 02:27:31,648
Charge!

1321
02:28:26,726 --> 02:28:30,203
Well, that was easy. Come on, Doctor,
let's see what we've done.

1322
02:29:14,281 --> 02:29:16,526
"St. Michael's Military School."

1323
02:29:22,407 --> 02:29:24,690
You old bastard!

1324
02:29:36,167 --> 02:29:37,520
It doesn't matter.

1325
02:29:41,124 --> 02:29:43,284
Did you ever love a woman, Razin?

1326
02:29:43,687 --> 02:29:45,921
I once had a wife and four children.

1327
02:29:58,648 --> 02:29:59,807
He has been a good comrade.

1328
02:29:59,845 --> 02:30:01,562
He's been a good medical officer.

1329
02:30:01,602 --> 02:30:04,326
We took him from his wife,
we took him from his child.

1330
02:30:04,640 --> 02:30:06,042
None of this matters.

1331
02:30:07,328 --> 02:30:09,686
What does matter, Comrade Commissar?

1332
02:30:10,079 --> 02:30:11,441
Tell me, I've forgotten.

1333
02:30:11,527 --> 02:30:13,646
This is contemptible. The doctor stays.

1334
02:30:13,724 --> 02:30:14,884
I command this unit!

1335
02:30:14,960 --> 02:30:17,684
We command jointly.
The "Party Bulletin" expressly states--

1336
02:30:20,524 --> 02:30:22,719
I could have you taken out and shot.

1337
02:30:23,639 --> 02:30:26,048
And could you have the Party
taken out and shot?

1338
02:30:26,566 --> 02:30:27,879
Try to understand.

1339
02:30:28,118 --> 02:30:31,648
As the military struggle nears its close,
the political struggle intensifies.

1340
02:30:32,002 --> 02:30:35,003
In the hour of victory
the military will have served its purpose.

1341
02:30:35,042 --> 02:30:37,201
All men will then be judged politically...

1342
02:30:37,805 --> 02:30:40,085
...regardless of their military record.

1343
02:30:41,437 --> 02:30:44,804
Meanwhile, there are still White units
in this area.

1344
02:30:44,880 --> 02:30:46,167
The doctor stays.

1345
02:30:46,886 --> 02:30:48,564
That concludes the meeting.

1346
02:31:38,644 --> 02:31:40,437
Comrade, where are you going?

1347
02:31:41,119 --> 02:31:42,958
Are you running away, Comrade?

1348
02:31:44,283 --> 02:31:45,404
Soldiers.

1349
02:31:45,760 --> 02:31:47,525
Red soldiers or White soldiers?

1350
02:31:47,602 --> 02:31:48,762
Soldiers.

1351
02:33:33,841 --> 02:33:34,955
Tonya!

1352
02:33:35,999 --> 02:33:37,034
Tonya!

1353
02:33:37,198 --> 02:33:38,195
Sasha!

1354
02:33:41,276 --> 02:33:42,196
Tonya!

1355
02:33:45,841 --> 02:33:46,799
Tonya!

1356
02:33:49,437 --> 02:33:50,358
Tonya!

1357
02:33:54,721 --> 02:33:55,680
Tonya!

1358
02:33:55,995 --> 02:33:56,955
Tonya!

1359
02:34:44,678 --> 02:34:45,963
This is Yuriatin?

1360
02:34:46,117 --> 02:34:47,716
Yes. Yuriatin.

1361
02:34:49,039 --> 02:34:50,881
What's happened at Varykino?

1362
02:34:50,958 --> 02:34:52,397
The Moscow folks?

1363
02:34:53,116 --> 02:34:53,921
Yes.

1364
02:34:53,960 --> 02:34:57,316
They've gone away. Gone away.
There's nobody at Varykino.

1365
02:35:48,318 --> 02:35:51,521
Lord what happiness!
They say you are alive.

1366
02:35:51,676 --> 02:35:53,479
Someone saw you near the Town.

1367
02:35:53,919 --> 02:35:57,716
I take it you have gone to Varykino,
so I'm going there myself with Katya.

1368
02:35:57,879 --> 02:36:01,361
But just in case, I've left a little food,
boiled potatoes mostly.

1369
02:36:01,437 --> 02:36:04,275
Put the lid back on the pan
or the rats will get it.

1370
02:36:04,361 --> 02:36:06,673
Oh, I'm mad with joy.

1371
02:37:19,674 --> 02:37:20,595
Tonya!

1372
02:37:22,311 --> 02:37:23,318
Tonya!

1373
02:37:24,201 --> 02:37:25,112
Yuri.

1374
02:37:25,160 --> 02:37:26,196
Tonya!

1375
02:37:26,475 --> 02:37:29,437
Yuri. Yuri, darling.

1376
02:37:44,198 --> 02:37:46,999
It's all right, Yuri. They're safe.

1377
02:37:47,956 --> 02:37:49,279
They're in Moscow.

1378
02:37:49,471 --> 02:37:50,919
- In Moscow?
- Yes.

1379
02:37:51,677 --> 02:37:53,154
- Tonya?
- All of them.

1380
02:37:53,719 --> 02:37:54,832
They're safe.

1381
02:37:56,356 --> 02:37:57,356
Safe.

1382
02:38:00,318 --> 02:38:01,718
Firing squad--

1383
02:38:38,439 --> 02:38:39,437
Better.

1384
02:38:48,319 --> 02:38:49,352
What?

1385
02:38:50,715 --> 02:38:52,912
I've got a letter for you.

1386
02:38:52,960 --> 02:38:54,600
I've had it three months.

1387
02:38:56,795 --> 02:38:58,916
And it was three months getting here.

1388
02:38:59,317 --> 02:39:00,591
It's from Moscow.

1389
02:39:03,076 --> 02:39:04,679
I think it's from Tonya.

1390
02:39:05,121 --> 02:39:07,192
It's addressed to you. Care of me.

1391
02:39:09,599 --> 02:39:12,638
She came into Yuriatin to find you
when you vanished.

1392
02:39:13,953 --> 02:39:15,477
Someone sent her here.

1393
02:39:15,795 --> 02:39:16,916
You met?

1394
02:39:20,034 --> 02:39:21,317
She's very fine.

1395
02:39:31,552 --> 02:39:33,037
My dearest dear...

1396
02:39:33,680 --> 02:39:36,115
...I am sending this to Larissa Antipova...

1397
02:39:36,317 --> 02:39:38,992
...because if you are alive,
which God grant...

1398
02:39:39,471 --> 02:39:41,397
...I think that is where you will go.

1399
02:39:42,310 --> 02:39:44,872
We have a little daughter, Yuri,
did you know?

1400
02:39:45,918 --> 02:39:47,317
Her name is Anna.

1401
02:39:47,834 --> 02:39:49,399
Father sends greetings.

1402
02:39:50,032 --> 02:39:51,796
Sasha has grown quite a lot.

1403
02:39:52,035 --> 02:39:53,435
He is quite big now.

1404
02:39:54,395 --> 02:39:57,875
Whenever we speak of you
he weeps and won't be comforted.

1405
02:39:58,911 --> 02:40:00,840
This is what I have to tell you.

1406
02:40:00,954 --> 02:40:02,998
We are being deported from Russia.

1407
02:40:03,675 --> 02:40:06,517
We can't make out
if you would be allowed to join us.

1408
02:40:07,072 --> 02:40:09,519
An organization in Paris
which I mustn't name...

1409
02:40:09,595 --> 02:40:11,110
...will know where we are...

1410
02:40:11,197 --> 02:40:13,798
...but nothing is certain
and there is very little time.

1411
02:40:13,874 --> 02:40:15,551
I am writing this in haste.

1412
02:40:16,356 --> 02:40:18,073
They are coming for us now.

1413
02:40:18,437 --> 02:40:19,635
God bless you.

1414
02:40:20,709 --> 02:40:23,749
I must honestly admit
that Antipova is a good person.

1415
02:40:34,558 --> 02:40:37,753
Yuri, when they got away to Moscow,
she left something here.

1416
02:41:13,313 --> 02:41:14,359
Yuri!

1417
02:41:38,871 --> 02:41:40,118
May I come in?

1418
02:41:42,477 --> 02:41:44,912
Yuri Andreyevich, you've changed, I think.

1419
02:41:46,352 --> 02:41:47,953
Oh, yes, decidedly.

1420
02:41:49,715 --> 02:41:50,713
Larissa...

1421
02:41:52,756 --> 02:41:54,274
...remarkably the same.

1422
02:42:01,754 --> 02:42:03,154
I came from Moscow.

1423
02:42:04,429 --> 02:42:06,233
I'm on my way to Vladivostock.

1424
02:42:13,750 --> 02:42:15,592
I'm here to offer you my help.

1425
02:42:15,668 --> 02:42:17,069
We don't want it.

1426
02:42:17,272 --> 02:42:18,556
Speak for yourself.

1427
02:42:18,633 --> 02:42:19,918
We don't want it.

1428
02:42:20,272 --> 02:42:23,831
Yuri Andreyevich, you spent two years
with the Partisans, Fifth Division.

1429
02:42:23,918 --> 02:42:26,352
You have no discharge
so you are a deserter.

1430
02:42:26,554 --> 02:42:30,150
Your family in Paris is involved
in a dangerous migr organization.

1431
02:42:30,352 --> 02:42:32,307
Now all these are technicalities.

1432
02:42:33,277 --> 02:42:34,915
But your style of life...

1433
02:42:34,991 --> 02:42:36,836
...everything you say and think...

1434
02:42:36,912 --> 02:42:40,191
...your published writings
are all flagrantly subversive.

1435
02:42:40,469 --> 02:42:41,996
Your days are numbered.

1436
02:42:42,551 --> 02:42:43,837
Unless I help you.

1437
02:42:44,555 --> 02:42:46,107
Do you want my help?

1438
02:42:47,029 --> 02:42:47,951
No.

1439
02:42:48,956 --> 02:42:50,030
Wait, Yuri.

1440
02:42:55,228 --> 02:42:57,068
Larissa, three glasses.

1441
02:42:57,673 --> 02:42:58,674
No!

1442
02:42:59,354 --> 02:43:02,077
Yuri, you must see how serious this is.

1443
02:43:05,549 --> 02:43:07,352
Please don't underestimate me.

1444
02:43:07,677 --> 02:43:11,032
Practically, or morally,
I am not the man you take me for.

1445
02:43:13,151 --> 02:43:15,272
How do you know all this about Yuri?

1446
02:43:15,674 --> 02:43:16,950
How can you help?

1447
02:43:17,430 --> 02:43:19,675
I do and I can. Isn't that sufficient?

1448
02:43:20,030 --> 02:43:20,991
No.

1449
02:43:23,156 --> 02:43:24,353
Sant, Larissa.

1450
02:43:34,749 --> 02:43:37,147
Our eastern seaboard is
an undeveloped area.

1451
02:43:38,355 --> 02:43:42,672
The Commissariat of Foreign Affairs wants
to establish an independent state there.

1452
02:43:43,190 --> 02:43:47,110
It affords us a temporary channel
of communication with the outside world.

1453
02:43:47,869 --> 02:43:50,506
I've good contacts in the Far East.

1454
02:43:51,793 --> 02:43:54,228
I've been appointed the minister of justice.

1455
02:43:54,670 --> 02:43:56,031
The Bolsheviks trust you?

1456
02:43:56,108 --> 02:43:59,473
They trust no one.
They've found me useful.

1457
02:44:04,357 --> 02:44:05,996
Here's how I can help you.

1458
02:44:06,752 --> 02:44:07,712
You...

1459
02:44:08,557 --> 02:44:10,752
You come with me
as far as the Pacific Coast.

1460
02:44:10,830 --> 02:44:13,150
And from there you can go where you like.

1461
02:44:13,957 --> 02:44:15,355
To Paris.

1462
02:44:15,433 --> 02:44:16,392
Or not.

1463
02:44:17,349 --> 02:44:18,952
I think you'd better go.

1464
02:44:19,556 --> 02:44:23,507
Your rarified selfishness is intolerable.

1465
02:44:24,430 --> 02:44:26,068
Larissa's in danger, too.

1466
02:44:26,874 --> 02:44:28,428
By association with me?

1467
02:44:28,552 --> 02:44:31,514
No. Not by association with you.
You're small fry.

1468
02:44:32,588 --> 02:44:34,593
By association with Strelnikov.

1469
02:44:35,034 --> 02:44:36,549
I've never met Strelnikov.

1470
02:44:36,626 --> 02:44:39,071
You're married to Strelnikov.
They know that.

1471
02:44:39,513 --> 02:44:41,354
I was married to Pasha Antipov.

1472
02:44:41,430 --> 02:44:44,787
I understand, I understand.
But they don't.

1473
02:44:45,593 --> 02:44:46,994
You're being watched.

1474
02:44:48,193 --> 02:44:49,469
Do you know why?

1475
02:44:50,869 --> 02:44:54,272
A husband is a sticky commodity, my dear.

1476
02:44:55,635 --> 02:44:56,747
Go away!

1477
02:44:59,508 --> 02:45:02,672
More of your high-minded lunacy.

1478
02:45:04,073 --> 02:45:05,866
You have a child to think of.

1479
02:45:06,433 --> 02:45:07,471
Look here.

1480
02:45:08,468 --> 02:45:09,514
Here.

1481
02:45:09,993 --> 02:45:11,470
That's sugar for the child.

1482
02:45:11,557 --> 02:45:12,832
I don't want it.

1483
02:45:14,193 --> 02:45:15,995
You'd refuse my sugar?

1484
02:45:17,433 --> 02:45:19,427
Who are you to refuse me anything?

1485
02:45:19,667 --> 02:45:20,713
Now you go!

1486
02:45:24,788 --> 02:45:26,073
- I came--
- Go!

1487
02:45:27,108 --> 02:45:28,105
Go!

1488
02:45:29,709 --> 02:45:31,867
I came to you in good faith.

1489
02:45:37,026 --> 02:45:39,384
You stay here then and get your desserts!

1490
02:45:42,953 --> 02:45:44,793
Your desserts, do you hear me?

1491
02:45:48,630 --> 02:45:50,434
You think you're immaculate.

1492
02:45:54,637 --> 02:45:56,111
You're not immaculate!

1493
02:45:58,392 --> 02:45:59,554
I know you!

1494
02:46:01,434 --> 02:46:03,027
Do you hear me?

1495
02:46:03,830 --> 02:46:08,186
We're all made of the same clay, you know.

1496
02:46:09,833 --> 02:46:10,832
Clay!

1497
02:46:12,310 --> 02:46:13,912
Clay!

1498
02:46:18,669 --> 02:46:19,713
Lara.

1499
02:46:22,713 --> 02:46:24,104
He's rubbish, Lara.

1500
02:46:25,629 --> 02:46:27,031
Yes, rubbish.

1501
02:46:29,666 --> 02:46:31,345
I wish he'd never happened.

1502
02:46:32,188 --> 02:46:33,467
Does it matter?

1503
02:46:34,433 --> 02:46:35,671
Doesn't it?

1504
02:46:36,112 --> 02:46:37,108
Not to me.

1505
02:46:46,632 --> 02:46:48,952
What shall we do? Can we get on a train?

1506
02:46:49,508 --> 02:46:51,466
No, they'd arrest us on the spot.

1507
02:46:52,347 --> 02:46:54,429
I don't want to stay here and wait.

1508
02:46:54,708 --> 02:46:55,668
No.

1509
02:46:58,314 --> 02:46:59,273
Listen.

1510
02:47:00,750 --> 02:47:02,590
- We could go to--
- Varykino.

1511
02:47:05,151 --> 02:47:07,070
They'd find out sooner or later.

1512
02:47:07,588 --> 02:47:08,785
Yes, but later.

1513
02:47:09,593 --> 02:47:11,624
And if our days are really numbered, Yuri--

1514
02:47:11,711 --> 02:47:13,992
Yes. We'd better live them.

1515
02:47:16,785 --> 02:47:18,423
Before we're parted.

1516
02:47:19,191 --> 02:47:20,152
Yes.

1517
02:49:52,905 --> 02:49:56,270
Anna taught me to write at this desk.

1518
02:53:41,418 --> 02:53:42,858
This isn't me, Yuri.

1519
02:53:44,184 --> 02:53:45,220
Yes, it is.

1520
02:53:46,188 --> 02:53:47,146
No.

1521
02:53:48,459 --> 02:53:49,419
It's you.

1522
02:53:54,741 --> 02:53:55,786
"Lara."

1523
02:54:43,978 --> 02:54:44,984
Yuri!

1524
02:54:46,059 --> 02:54:47,861
Yuri, there's a wolf howling!

1525
02:54:48,065 --> 02:54:49,703
Oh, yes.

1526
02:54:53,625 --> 02:54:56,616
I've seen them. They're frightened.
They won't harm us.

1527
02:54:57,060 --> 02:54:58,900
Yes. I know.

1528
02:55:00,300 --> 02:55:01,347
I'm sorry.

1529
02:55:10,027 --> 02:55:12,942
Oh, Lord, this is an awful time to be alive.

1530
02:55:13,546 --> 02:55:14,505
No.

1531
02:55:14,581 --> 02:55:15,942
It is. Oh, it is!

1532
02:55:15,982 --> 02:55:16,940
No. No.

1533
02:56:20,065 --> 02:56:22,344
Wouldn't it have been lovely
if we'd met before?

1534
02:56:22,383 --> 02:56:23,621
Before we did?

1535
02:56:24,705 --> 02:56:25,664
Yes.

1536
02:56:28,137 --> 02:56:30,861
We'd have got married
and had a house and children.

1537
02:56:34,065 --> 02:56:37,739
If we'd had children, Yuri,
would you have liked a boy or a girl?

1538
02:56:39,138 --> 02:56:42,984
I think we may go mad,
if we think about all that.

1539
02:56:43,616 --> 02:56:45,496
I shall always think about it.

1540
02:56:46,895 --> 02:56:49,063
- Will you write today?
- No, not today.

1541
02:57:07,976 --> 02:57:08,945
Katya!

1542
02:57:10,738 --> 02:57:12,176
Come to me, darling.

1543
02:57:24,703 --> 02:57:25,661
Victor!

1544
02:57:27,340 --> 02:57:28,738
We thought it was--

1545
02:57:30,176 --> 02:57:31,137
Quiet.

1546
02:57:33,545 --> 02:57:35,500
I wonder if you'd mind, Comrades?

1547
02:57:39,900 --> 02:57:42,854
There's a train belonging
to my government standing in Yuriatin.

1548
02:57:42,942 --> 02:57:45,463
It has a carriage for myself
and my assistants.

1549
02:57:45,578 --> 02:57:48,303
You would travel in comfort and safety.

1550
02:57:48,582 --> 02:57:50,701
There's no question.
I'm not going with you.

1551
02:57:50,779 --> 02:57:53,702
I'm not going without you.
So, there's an end to it.

1552
02:57:54,334 --> 02:57:57,374
Well, then, I'll have to speak
to Yuri Andreyevich in private.

1553
02:58:12,425 --> 02:58:13,861
Strelnikov is dead.

1554
02:58:14,657 --> 02:58:15,501
What?

1555
02:58:15,540 --> 02:58:17,620
Spare me your expressions of regret.

1556
02:58:17,736 --> 02:58:21,102
He was a murderous neurotic
and no loss to anyone.

1557
02:58:21,982 --> 02:58:24,057
Do you see how this affects Larissa?

1558
02:58:24,382 --> 02:58:25,380
You don't.

1559
02:58:26,462 --> 02:58:27,622
You're a fool.

1560
02:58:32,140 --> 02:58:33,579
She's Strelnikov's wife.

1561
02:58:33,656 --> 02:58:36,781
Why do you think they haven't
arrested her? Is this the usual practice?

1562
02:58:36,858 --> 02:58:39,216
Why do you think
they had her watched in Yuriatin?

1563
02:58:39,293 --> 02:58:41,297
They were waiting for Strelnikov.

1564
02:58:41,662 --> 02:58:44,338
If they thought that he would
come running to his wife...

1565
02:58:44,414 --> 02:58:45,739
...they didn't know him.

1566
02:58:45,816 --> 02:58:47,179
They knew him well enough.

1567
02:58:47,216 --> 02:58:50,103
He was only five miles from here
when they caught him.

1568
02:58:50,296 --> 02:58:53,297
He was arrested on the open road.
He didn't conceal his identity.

1569
02:58:53,383 --> 02:58:56,613
Throughout the entire interview,
he insisted they call him Pavel Antipov...

1570
02:58:56,661 --> 02:59:00,181
...which is his right name, and refused
to answer to the name of Strelnikov.

1571
02:59:00,296 --> 02:59:03,137
On his way to execution,
he took a pistol from one of the guards...

1572
02:59:03,176 --> 02:59:04,776
...and blew his own brains out.

1573
02:59:05,419 --> 02:59:06,704
Oh, my God!

1574
02:59:08,624 --> 02:59:09,821
Don't tell Lara this.

1575
02:59:10,138 --> 02:59:12,699
I think I know Lara at least as well as you.

1576
02:59:12,775 --> 02:59:15,977
But don't you see her position?
She's served her purpose.

1577
02:59:16,179 --> 02:59:18,539
These men that came with me today
as an escort...

1578
02:59:18,578 --> 02:59:21,540
...will come for her and the child tomorrow,
as a firing squad.

1579
02:59:21,980 --> 02:59:24,501
Now, I know exactly what you think of me.

1580
02:59:24,617 --> 02:59:25,614
And why.

1581
02:59:26,256 --> 02:59:28,982
But if you're not coming with me,
she's not coming with me.

1582
02:59:29,903 --> 02:59:31,783
So, are you coming with me?

1583
02:59:32,339 --> 02:59:34,898
Do you accept the protection
of this ignoble Caliban...

1584
02:59:34,974 --> 02:59:37,738
...on any terms that Caliban cares to make?

1585
02:59:38,139 --> 02:59:43,617
Or, is your delicacy so exorbitant that you
would sacrifice a woman and a child to it?

1586
02:59:52,814 --> 02:59:55,057
There are some bags to carry, Comrades.

1587
03:00:11,179 --> 03:00:12,216
Get in!

1588
03:00:16,943 --> 03:00:17,853
Come.

1589
03:00:21,939 --> 03:00:23,177
- How many?
- All of us.

1590
03:00:23,253 --> 03:00:24,536
Sorry, not enough room.

1591
03:00:24,615 --> 03:00:26,378
Comrade, there's got to be room.

1592
03:00:26,416 --> 03:00:28,498
It's all right, I have to bring our sledge.

1593
03:00:28,574 --> 03:00:31,538
Hurry. This train can't wait.
There are important people on it.

1594
03:00:31,614 --> 03:00:33,295
You start, I'll catch you up.

1595
03:00:39,173 --> 03:00:40,460
Right, Comrades!

1596
03:00:42,855 --> 03:00:44,141
We'll see you.

1597
03:00:45,100 --> 03:00:46,222
Hurry!

1598
03:02:18,058 --> 03:02:21,251
I'm afraid that's it, my dear.
Your young man's not coming.

1599
03:02:21,817 --> 03:02:22,776
You fool!

1600
03:02:24,050 --> 03:02:26,536
Did you really think
he would come with you?

1601
03:02:35,617 --> 03:02:37,017
The man's an idiot.

1602
03:02:39,012 --> 03:02:41,054
From Mongolia
he could have gone to China.

1603
03:02:41,131 --> 03:02:42,658
He'll never leave Russia.

1604
03:02:42,734 --> 03:02:45,296
Let him stay.
You've come with me, haven't you?

1605
03:02:46,733 --> 03:02:47,655
Yes.

1606
03:02:49,255 --> 03:02:51,655
To be sure, it was your duty as a mother.

1607
03:02:52,852 --> 03:02:54,338
That's right, Victor.

1608
03:02:57,054 --> 03:02:58,981
I'm carrying Yuri's child.

1609
03:03:04,457 --> 03:03:07,661
I was born out there,
in the Far East, somewhere.

1610
03:03:08,101 --> 03:03:10,575
I think it was Mongolia. I don't remember.

1611
03:03:10,651 --> 03:03:13,412
You were born in Mongolia.
And you were born that very year.

1612
03:03:13,500 --> 03:03:15,292
So were a lot of other children.

1613
03:03:15,330 --> 03:03:18,698
Not many called Tonya, bearing the name
Komarov, or Komarovsky.

1614
03:03:18,937 --> 03:03:20,817
Komarov's a common name. So is Tonya.

1615
03:03:20,893 --> 03:03:23,414
With fair hair and blue eyes,
lost at the age of eight...

1616
03:03:23,492 --> 03:03:25,738
...when the civil war broke out
in the Far East.

1617
03:03:25,814 --> 03:03:27,695
There's something you haven't told me.

1618
03:03:27,781 --> 03:03:29,574
How did you come to be lost?

1619
03:03:30,177 --> 03:03:31,338
I can't remember.

1620
03:03:31,414 --> 03:03:33,371
I don't believe that.
You must remember something.

1621
03:03:33,459 --> 03:03:34,253
No!

1622
03:03:35,980 --> 03:03:38,136
Shall I tell you
how I first met your mother?

1623
03:03:38,213 --> 03:03:40,093
If she was my mother, Comrade General.

1624
03:03:40,132 --> 03:03:41,139
You doubt it?

1625
03:03:41,292 --> 03:03:44,535
I picked my brother up, literally picked
him up, on a Moscow street.

1626
03:03:44,611 --> 03:03:47,938
He had a fourth-class ration book
and he was undernourished.

1627
03:03:48,178 --> 03:03:50,539
He didn't seem to mind that, or anything.

1628
03:03:50,931 --> 03:03:53,251
I thought he was a happier man than me.

1629
03:03:54,574 --> 03:03:56,732
He suffered me to buy him a new suit.

1630
03:03:57,490 --> 03:03:59,859
And to get him a job at his old hospital.

1631
03:04:00,654 --> 03:04:02,899
I saw him off for his first day's work.

1632
03:04:03,292 --> 03:04:07,617
This was eight years
after he and Lara parted.

1633
03:04:09,096 --> 03:04:10,620
So, he never saw her again?

1634
03:04:15,538 --> 03:04:17,811
Thank you. You've been very kind to me.

1635
03:04:24,611 --> 03:04:28,456
He must have known how ill he was.
The walls of his heart were like paper.

1636
03:04:28,898 --> 03:04:32,734
But, he kept it to himself.
He kept a lot to himself.

1637
03:04:56,652 --> 03:04:57,612
Please!

1638
03:06:01,177 --> 03:06:04,214
I was astonished at the extent
of his reputation.

1639
03:06:05,049 --> 03:06:09,097
His work was unobtainable at the time.
It was disapproved ofby the Party.

1640
03:06:09,893 --> 03:06:12,453
But, ifpeople love poetry, they love poets.

1641
03:06:13,412 --> 03:06:15,253
And nobody loves poetry like a Russian.

1642
03:06:25,333 --> 03:06:26,695
Excuse me, Comrade.

1643
03:06:27,932 --> 03:06:29,208
Are you Yevgraf?.

1644
03:06:30,368 --> 03:06:31,578
My name's Lara.

1645
03:06:31,894 --> 03:06:33,851
I knew her name from the Lara poems...

1646
03:06:33,888 --> 03:06:36,449
...which I'd found
among my brother's manuscripts.

1647
03:06:37,169 --> 03:06:38,656
I knew your brother.

1648
03:06:40,335 --> 03:06:41,694
I need your help.

1649
03:06:42,251 --> 03:06:44,774
She'd come to Moscow
to look for her child.

1650
03:06:45,214 --> 03:06:47,094
I helped her as far as I could.

1651
03:06:50,692 --> 03:06:52,415
But, I knew it was hopeless.

1652
03:06:58,055 --> 03:07:00,375
I think I was a little in love with her.

1653
03:07:08,577 --> 03:07:10,974
One day she went away
and didn't come back.

1654
03:07:11,492 --> 03:07:14,013
She died, or vanished, somewhere...

1655
03:07:14,091 --> 03:07:15,971
...in one of the labor camps...

1656
03:07:16,374 --> 03:07:20,053
...a nameless number on a list
that was afterwards mislaid.

1657
03:07:21,256 --> 03:07:23,490
That was quite common in those days.

1658
03:07:33,491 --> 03:07:35,333
How did you come to be lost?

1659
03:07:37,212 --> 03:07:39,331
- We were running in the street.
- We?

1660
03:07:39,408 --> 03:07:41,853
- My father.
- Not your father, Komarovsky.

1661
03:07:41,931 --> 03:07:43,092
I don't know.

1662
03:07:43,696 --> 03:07:45,375
The street was under fire.

1663
03:07:45,576 --> 03:07:48,933
There were explosions
and the houses were falling down...

1664
03:07:50,936 --> 03:07:52,654
...and he let go of my hand.

1665
03:07:54,407 --> 03:07:55,854
He let go of my hand.

1666
03:07:57,850 --> 03:07:59,049
And I was lost.

1667
03:08:02,607 --> 03:08:04,450
Would a father have done that?

1668
03:08:04,929 --> 03:08:07,768
Oh, yes, people will do anything.

1669
03:08:08,132 --> 03:08:09,455
It was Komarovsky.

1670
03:08:12,975 --> 03:08:16,255
This man was your father.

1671
03:08:18,690 --> 03:08:20,330
Why won't you believe it?

1672
03:08:21,567 --> 03:08:23,331
Don't you want to believe it?

1673
03:08:24,214 --> 03:08:25,857
Not if it isn't true.

1674
03:08:29,530 --> 03:08:30,814
That's inherited.

1675
03:08:31,256 --> 03:08:34,773
Comrade General, when I was a child,
I wanted parents.

1676
03:08:35,973 --> 03:08:38,208
You can imagine how I wanted parents.

1677
03:08:39,732 --> 03:08:43,289
I wanted to die when I was a child,
you know?

1678
03:08:46,846 --> 03:08:48,171
Now, I don't know.

1679
03:08:50,330 --> 03:08:52,851
I can't be of any use to them, now, can I?

1680
03:08:53,772 --> 03:08:56,169
I was hoping I might be
of some use to you.

1681
03:08:58,489 --> 03:09:00,092
Will you think about it?

1682
03:09:00,168 --> 03:09:01,129
Yes.

1683
03:09:06,852 --> 03:09:08,330
It's all right, David.

1684
03:09:11,686 --> 03:09:12,733
Do you work here?

1685
03:09:12,809 --> 03:09:14,536
Yes, Comrade General. I'm an operator.

1686
03:09:14,612 --> 03:09:16,051
And what do you operate?

1687
03:09:17,412 --> 03:09:18,335
That!

1688
03:09:33,611 --> 03:09:35,374
You've promised to think about it.

1689
03:09:47,964 --> 03:09:48,924
Tonya!

1690
03:09:50,765 --> 03:09:52,370
Can you play the balalaika?

1691
03:09:52,609 --> 03:09:53,769
Can she play?

1692
03:09:54,249 --> 03:09:55,534
She's an artist!

1693
03:09:55,735 --> 03:09:57,933
An artist? Who taught you?

1694
03:09:58,689 --> 03:10:00,213
No one taught her.

1695
03:10:02,208 --> 03:10:03,494
Then, it's a gift.

